{% comment %}
  Preorder confirmation — the richer "thank you" rendered after a successful
  POST /preorder/cart/submit.js when a thank-you URL is configured. The submit
  flow redirects here with `?cart=<cartId>` (see preorder-page.js), and
  preorder-confirmation.js fills the panel from
  GET /preorder/cart/confirmation.js?cart_id=<cartId>: the real per-date order
  number(s), the umbrella Preorder id, delivery address, item count, total,
  discount, per-date delivery dates, and the asynchronously-generated PDF
  (generating… → download link, broadcast-driven when a pusher key is set,
  polling otherwise).

  While the queued submit/edit is still processing, the endpoint returns a slim
  `processing: true` block instead of the previous submission's (stale) data;
  the panel then shows a "we are processing your preorder" spinner state and
  swaps to the real details when PreorderProcessedEvent arrives on the pusher
  channel (or the poll sees processing end).

  Background color: the page gutters take the current selected brand's
  `color_schema.preorderConfirmation.bg` (exposed on
  `customer.aico_selected_brand.aico_preorder_confirmation_bg_color`), applied
  at render time as the `--aico-confirmation-bg` custom property so there is no
  flash. The centered white card stays readable on any brand color; when the
  brand sets no color we fall back to the default page background.

  All names on this surface are aico_*-prefixed — there is no Shopify equivalent
  for a B2B preorder confirmation PDF. The pusher publics are NOT theme settings:
  the backend embeds them (key / cluster / channel) in the confirmation payload,
  sourced from aico's broadcasting config; when broadcasting is off the JS polls
  and the same UI is shown.

  Note: {% render %} does not resolve to files in this theme (BlankFileSystem),
  so the panel markup is inlined; it is identical to the inline reveal embedded
  on templates/aico-preorder.liquid.
{% endcomment %}

{%- assign aico_confirmation_bg = customer.aico_selected_brand.aico_preorder_confirmation_bg_color -%}

<main class="aico-preorder-thank-you" role="main"{% if aico_confirmation_bg %} style="--aico-confirmation-bg: {{ aico_confirmation_bg | escape }};"{% endif %}>
  <div class="aico-page-container">
  {%- comment -%}
    The panel server-renders in the PROCESSING state (--processing class +
    processing copy + aria-busy) so the page never flashes the confirmed
    checkmark before preorder-confirmation.js has verified the data: the JS
    swaps to the confirmed details only once confirmation.js returns them
    (or to the generic thank-you copy when there is no cart id to confirm).
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <section
    class="aico-preorder-confirmation aico-preorder-confirmation--processing"
    aria-busy="true"
    data-aico-preorder-confirmation
    data-aico-confirmation-autostart="1"
    data-aico-confirmation-url="{{ routes.aico_preorder_cart_confirmation_url }}"
    data-aico-confirmation-title="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.title' | t | escape }}"
    data-aico-confirmation-message="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.message' | t | escape }}"
    data-aico-confirmation-processing-title="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.processing_title' | t | escape }}"
    data-aico-confirmation-processing-message="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.processing_message' | t | escape }}"
    data-aico-confirmation-almost-there="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.almost_there' | t | escape }}"
    data-aico-confirmation-error-title="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.error_title' | t | escape }}"
    data-aico-confirmation-error-message="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.error_message' | t | escape }}"
    data-aico-confirmation-missing-title="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.missing_title' | t | escape }}"
    data-aico-confirmation-missing-message="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.missing_message' | t | escape }}"
    data-aico-confirmation-update-title="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.update_title' | t | escape }}"
    data-aico-confirmation-update-message="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.update_message' | t | escape }}"
    data-aico-confirmation-number-pending="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.number_pending' | t | escape }}"
    data-aico-confirmation-pcs="{{ 'aico_preorder.catalog.pcs' | t | escape }}"
    data-aico-confirmation-pdf-generating="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.pdf_generating' | t | escape }}"
    data-aico-confirmation-pdf-download="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.pdf_download' | t | escape }}"
    data-aico-confirmation-pdf-unavailable="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.pdf_unavailable' | t | escape }}">

    {%- comment -%} Status medallion — the same component the checkout thank-you
      uses (.aico-ty-status), so both post-submit surfaces wait and resolve
      identically. Here it doubles as the submit progress ring: it sweeps while
      the count is unknown or complete, and becomes a determinate arc in between.
      It sits OUTSIDE the header because the processing → confirmed swap fades
      the panel body out and back in; the medallion has to stay put for its own
      spinner → checkmark hand-off to be visible across that swap. {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="aico-ty-status" aria-hidden="true" data-aico-confirmation-status>
      <svg class="aico-ty-status-svg" viewBox="0 0 52 52" focusable="false" role="presentation">
        <circle class="aico-ty-status-track" cx="26" cy="26" r="24"/>
        <circle class="aico-ty-status-spin" cx="26" cy="26" r="24"/>
        <circle class="aico-ty-status-ring" cx="26" cy="26" r="24"/>
        <circle class="aico-ty-status-disc" cx="26" cy="26" r="24"/>
        <path class="aico-ty-status-check" d="M14.1 27.2l7.1 7.2 16.7-16.8"/>
        {%- comment -%} Third state on the same geometry: the page was opened
          with no `?cart=` to confirm against (a locale switch used to drop it,
          and a bare visit or an old bookmark never had one). It replaces what
          was previously the worst possible answer here — the full success
          skeleton, checkmark and all, with "…" where the order number goes.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <circle class="aico-ty-status-warn-disc" cx="26" cy="26" r="24"/>
        <path class="aico-ty-status-warn-triangle" d="M26 15.4 38.4 36.6 13.6 36.6 Z"/>
        <path class="aico-ty-status-warn-bang" d="M26 22.6V29.4"/>
        <circle class="aico-ty-status-warn-dot" cx="26" cy="33.1" r="1.45"/>
      </svg>
    </div>

    {%- comment -%}
      Real submit progress, on both submit flows (first submit and edit
      re-submit). The count is seeded from the confirmation endpoint's
      processing block (0 / X) on the very first request and then advanced by
      PreorderSubmitProgressEvent; the medallion above carries the same
      fraction on its ring. Stays hidden when no counter exists at all. The
      count template keeps its {{ processed }}/{{ total }} placeholders (the t
      filter only interpolates args it is given) for client-side substitution.

      It sits directly under the medallion — NOT in the header — so the count
      reads as the spinner's own caption: the two are the only moving parts of
      the wait state, and the title/message between them made the number look
      like a footnote to the copy instead of the spinner's progress.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="aico-preorder-confirmation-progress" data-aico-confirmation-progress hidden
      role="progressbar"
      aria-valuemin="0"
      aria-valuemax="100"
      aria-valuenow="0"
      aria-label="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.processing_title' | t | escape }}"
      data-aico-confirmation-progress-template="{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.progress_count' | t | escape }}">
      <span class="aico-preorder-confirmation-progress-count" data-aico-confirmation-progress-count></span>
    </div>

    <header class="aico-preorder-confirmation-head">
      <h1 class="aico-preorder-confirmation-title" data-aico-confirmation-header>{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.processing_title' | t }}</h1>
      <p class="aico-preorder-confirmation-message" data-aico-confirmation-message>{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.processing_message' | t }}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="aico-preorder-confirmation-number-box">
      <span class="aico-preorder-confirmation-number-label">{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.number_label' | t }}</span>
      <span class="aico-preorder-confirmation-number" data-aico-confirmation-number>…</span>
      <span class="aico-preorder-confirmation-reference">
        {{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.reference_label' | t }}
        <span data-aico-confirmation-reference></span>
      </span>
    </div>

    <div class="aico-preorder-confirmation-summary">
      <div class="aico-preorder-confirmation-address">
        <span class="aico-preorder-confirmation-summary-label">{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.delivery_address' | t }}</span>
        <div class="aico-preorder-confirmation-address-value" data-aico-confirmation-address>—</div>
      </div>
      <dl class="aico-preorder-confirmation-totals">
        <div class="aico-preorder-confirmation-total-row">
          <dt>{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.item_count' | t }}</dt>
          <dd data-aico-confirmation-item-count>0</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="aico-preorder-confirmation-total-row" data-aico-confirmation-discount-row>
          <dt>{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.discount' | t }}</dt>
          <dd data-aico-confirmation-discount>&ndash;</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="aico-preorder-confirmation-total-row aico-preorder-confirmation-total-row--grand">
          <dt>{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.total' | t }}</dt>
          <dd data-aico-confirmation-total>&mdash;</dd>
        </div>
        {%- comment -%} The same total with VAT added — the net figure above is what
          the tier discount and the price list produce; this is what the invoice will
          say. Both come from the confirmation endpoint; the theme never does money
          arithmetic of its own. {%- endcomment -%}
        <div class="aico-preorder-confirmation-total-row aico-preorder-confirmation-total-row--vat">
          <dt>{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.total_with_vat' | t }}</dt>
          <dd data-aico-confirmation-total-with-vat>&mdash;</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </div>

    <div class="aico-preorder-confirmation-dates-wrap">
      <h2 class="aico-preorder-confirmation-dates-title">{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.delivery_dates' | t }}</h2>
      <div class="aico-preorder-confirmation-dates" data-aico-confirmation-dates></div>
    </div>

    <div class="aico-preorder-confirmation-pdf-area" data-aico-confirmation-pdf aria-live="polite" aria-busy="true">
      <span class="aico-preorder-confirmation-pdf-spinner" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      <span>{{ 'aico_preorder.confirmation.pdf_generating' | t }}</span>
    </div>

    <p class="aico-preorder-confirmation-links">
      <a class="aico-btn aico-btn-primary" href="{{ routes.aico_preorder_url }}">{{ 'aico_preorder.thank_you.back_to_preorder' | t }}</a>
      <a class="aico-btn aico-btn-secondary" href="{{ routes.root_url }}">{{ 'aico_preorder.thank_you.continue_shopping' | t }}</a>
    </p>
  </section>
  </div>

  <script src="{{ 'preorder-confirmation.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>
</main>
